This paper deals with the design and analysis of revenue-maximizing auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic economics (cs.EC). The paper also involves the use of statistical techniques to analyze the performance of auctions based on prior distributions (cs.DS, cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms (such as the empirical Myerson auction) to maximize revenue (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.EC, and cs.LG.
